Terribly sorry, sworn to secrecy.

529
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,540
(EXHALES)

530
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:55,260
Perhaps a brisk walk down the stairs

531
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:58,225
will do some good. Yes.

532
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:04,751
So it's that sort of Goya.

533
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,060
ON PHONE: Romanov.

534
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:08,261
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

535
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,666
That painted lady
you've been searching for,

536
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:15,505
I believe she may be in play.

537
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,665
I want that painting.

538
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:26,501
MARTLAND: Johanna!

539
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:28,106
Alastair.

540
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:30,105
So glad you called.

541
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:34,470
I've asked for a Chardonnay.
That is your drink, isn't it?

542
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,510
- Oh, you remembered.
- Mmm.

543
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,420
Thank you. (CLEARS THROAT)

544
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:41,460
Oh, God. How thoughtless of me.

545
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,946
You're on duty.

546
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:45,866
And in charge, thank you very much.

547
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:48,300
Mmm.

548
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,260
To what do I owe the pleasure?

549
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:52,660
I was just in the neighborhood
and thought I'd pop 'round,

550
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:55,140
and see how
you secret agent men run the world.

551
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:57,140
(CHUCKLES) Not nearly.

552
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:59,660
Although it is terribly vital work.

553
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:02,830
It's not all chardonnay
and afternoon trysts.

554
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:04,541
Is this a tryst?

555
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:09,386
No, no. No, no, no, no, no.
(CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY)

556
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:13,702
No, no, no, no.
No, no, no, no. No, no, no.

557
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:17,227
- No, I was just, um...
- Of course you were.

558
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,221
How are things at home?

559
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,780
(INHALES)

560
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:23,700
You've touched a nerve.

561
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,340
You've sensed it, Alastair.

562
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:27,224
You always were the sensitive one.

563
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:29,660
- You've got a difficult chap.
- Beastly.

564
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,140
Bit of a moron, actually.

565
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,183
Maybe I should have an affair.
(CHUCKLES)

566
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:35,543
- Wouldn't that be funny?
- Hilarious.

567
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,460
Do you think I could keep it a secret?

568
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:39,822
- Yes!
- Well then, what's the point?

569
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:41,940
Now, tell me,
what are you and my husband

570
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:43,426
working on at the moment?

571
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:46,820
Oh, uh... Well, in vague terms

572
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,700
there's a very bad man who wants
what I want, and I'm trying to stop him.

573
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,060
And what does a missing Goya

574
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:53,581
have to do with national security?

575
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,181
In vague terms.

576
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:57,460
- Johanna...
- (GASPS)

577
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:00,340
You think poor
Miss Fellworthy stumbled into something,

578
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,110
and that's why she got killed.

579
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,025
I really can't say.

580
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,263
Oh, this is interesting.

581
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:10,060
Creates quite a market when a painting
with a little mystery goes missing.

582
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:11,300
So much to do.

583
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:13,740
What was the name of
Bronwen's college at Oxford?

584
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:16,625
Johanna, I simply can't.

585
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:19,270
Right. Sorry.

586
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:23,420
Oh, golly. Look at the time.
I really must be going.

587
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:24,580
Oh.

588
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,900
It was lovely to see you, Alastair.

589
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,546
Thank you ever-so-much
for letting me confide in you.

590
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,102
I feel that I could share
anything with you.

591
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:36,706
Don't you feel the same?
That you could share with me?

592
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,391
Bronwen's college?

593
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,780
You're rather monstrous.

594
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,106
Of course you're aware of that.

595
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:45,146
- Blackfriar's Hall.
- We must do this again.

596
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,106
(SIGHS)

597
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:48,621
Hopeless.

598
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,460
MORTDECAI: Besides being
the finest garage man

599
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:58,991
in Western Civilization,

600
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:02,902
Spinoza was the best
art smuggler in the business,

601
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:07,986
and the eyes and ears
of the art world's underbelly.

602
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:12,860
Ah! Hello, Spinoza, you handsome devil!

603
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:14,780
It's a fine day to be alive, what?

604
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:16,980
You bloody chicken, bloody monkey,

605
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:19,620
so good-for-nothing pot of piss, innit?

606
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:22,664
Spinoza, you silver-tongued scallywag.

607
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:24,300
What's the matter with you, eh?

608
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:27,460
You one book short of a library,
you maggot? Eh?

609
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:28,980
You one megabyte short of a RAM?

610
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:31,500
MORTDECAI: The rest was a bit rude,
so I won't quote him verbatim.

611
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:35,420
But what vexed him so was a matter
of some overdue bills on the Rolls,

612
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:37,500
which I had now asked him to package

613
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:40,146
and ship off to America on credit.

614
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:43,181
You mother-loving bastard! Hello.

615
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:44,500
Right.

616
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,820
Uh, Spinoza,
I did not come here to discuss

617
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:48,820
my relationship with my mother, uh,

618
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,829
nor my relationship to your mother.

619
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,340
Uh, no. We have two items of business.

620
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:55,620
Item one: The Rolls-Royce,

621
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,820
which I have reluctantly agreed to sell

622
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:00,785
to that thick-fingered American, Krampf.

623
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:05,300
Item the second: I need to ascertain

624
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:08,620
whether any unsavory types
have enlisted you

625
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:11,346
to smuggle a painting
out of the country recently.

626
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:16,223
And for your information,
I am holding up

627
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:19,187
a 50-pound note.

628
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,540
Never mind about that.

629
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,823
You should treat a jam jar car like this

630
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:27,460
with more respect when you drive it

631
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:29,344
down the frog and toad road.

632
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:31,821
It's not some Toyota Clitoris.

633
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,140
- No, no.
- No!

634
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:36,025
Is a Rolls... The bloody Silver,

635
00:31:36,280 --> 00:31:38,826
the whacking Cloud, the bollock Royce!

636
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,380
Someone shooting at the bloody car!

637
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:42,980
- Ooh.
- (GROANS)

638
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:44,540
- (SCREAMS)
- Someone shooting at me!

639
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:46,020
(GUNFIRE)

640
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:47,140
(GROANS)

641
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:48,341
(MORTDECAI EXCLAIMS)

642
00:31:54,840 --> 00:31:56,066
MORTDECAI: I'm armed!

643
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,107
(MAN GROANS)

644
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:05,740
- Oh, Jock!
- Yeah.

645
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:06,860
Oops.

646
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:08,740
I should probably mention

647
00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:11,261
that this was not
the first time I had shot Jock.

648
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:15,469
Come on, you little bastards.
Come out and get it.

649
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:17,824
- (SCREAMS)
- (GUNSHOTS)

650
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:19,307
Oh!

651
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:22,781
(SQUAWKING)

652
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:28,261
Oh, afraid I'm all thumbs
with these damn things!

653
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:30,060
- Ohh!
- (THUDS)

654
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,220
Oh.

655
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:32,780
I believe I've just shot Jock.

656
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,141
Quite.

657
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:37,100
Man down! Man down!

658
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,620
Could you give me the gun, please?

659
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:39,780
This bit?

660
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,823
- Yes, most... No, no.
- (GRUNTS)

661
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:44,860
Oh, and poor Spinoza...

662
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:46,860
You should go, sir, before
the shooter circles 'round.

663
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:48,260
I'll handle things on this end.

664
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:49,621
Quite.

665
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,665
Cover me, as it were?

666
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:52,987
Yes, sir.

667
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,780
That's the old feudal spirit, Jock.

668
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:58,141
Get in.

669
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,310
- (GUNFIRE)
- MORTDECAI: Oh, dear!

670
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:03,140
(SCREAMS) Oh!

671
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,341
(SIGHS)

672
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:05,580
Oh, Jock.

673
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:07,100
- Jock?
- Yeah?

674
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,631
The door? Please?

675
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:15,660
(SIGHS) Right. Gosh, it's been ages.

676
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:17,021
(ENGINE STARTS)

677
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,300
(TIRES SCREECHING)

678
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,706
(SCREAMING)

679
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:27,705
(GRUMBLING IN ANNOYANCE)

680
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,626
(JOCK MOANING)

681
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,340
Goodness, that's awkward.

682
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:36,941
It's all right, sir. It's all right.
It's just a cracked rib.

683
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,580
Please, sir, if you wouldn't mind
leaving out the back. On foot.

684
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:42,140
(STAMMERING) By myself?

685
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,260
Please, sir. Just leave.

686
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:44,621
(CONTINUES GRUMBLING)

687
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:48,227
(GUN CLICKING)

688
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:51,140
Oh, dear, oh, dear, oh, dear,
oh, dear, oh, dear...

689
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:52,546
Oh!

690
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:53,940
Give me the painting.

691
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:56,142
(STAMMERING) What makes
you think I have it?

692
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:57,825
Give me the painting!

693
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,180
Ooh...

694
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:01,540
That is a superb Hulihee sans sideburn,

695
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,860
I must say.

696
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:04,700
I was admiring your Franz Joseph.

697
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:05,901
Oh, thank you very much.

698
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,100
- Oh!
- I'll have it on my wall.

699
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:09,381
Jock?

700
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:10,980
(GROANS)

701
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:12,340
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

702
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:14,224
- Oh, well done.
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

703
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,340
What should I do now?

704
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,860
- Run, sir!
- Again?

705
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:20,550
- Yes!
- Oh...

706
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:26,106
Run, I shall, like a bloody gazelle!

707
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:27,700
The Mortdecai men have always

708
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,823
been in tip-top shape, don't you know?

709
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:31,546
Fit as a fiddle!

710
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,106
(YELLING)

711
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,786
(SCREAMING)

712
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:47,062
(PANTING) Oh, it's burning...
I... I can't go on...

713
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:51,780
(GROANING)

714
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:53,421
Want to die...

715
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,386
No, I don't.

716
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,226
(SCREAMING)

717
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:00,461
Sir!

718
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,950
I'm on the bonnet!

719
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:05,024
Get in the car, sir!

720
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:07,141
(GRUNTING)

721
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:10,145
I don't like it!

722
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,260
(TIRES SCREECHING)

723
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,420
(SCREAMING)

724
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:15,781
Oh!

725
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,746
Ah! Oh!

726
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,141
Oh! Hello!

727
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:20,986
(GROANING)

728
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,061
(TIRES SCREECHING)

729
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:30,742
Jockie! Advise?

730
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,949
- Get in the back seat, sir!
- Okay!

731
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,305
Whoa.

732
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,661
Ha! Foreigner!

733
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:43,786
(YELPS) No!

734
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,505
Out you go!

735
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:49,581
(HORN HONKING)

736
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:54,940
(BOTH GROANING)

737
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:56,220
- Oh, Jock!
- Oh.

738
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,460
Don't worry, sir. I'm all right.
I am all right.

739
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:01,100
No, no, man! My little sproutling.

740
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,189
- What?
- Has it been compromised?

741
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:07,781
(SIREN WAILS)

742
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:16,780
MORTDECAI: Well done, Jock.

743
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,266
JOCK: It's a privilege, sir.

744
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,184
Didn't take long for you
to make a mess of things.

745
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:22,980
Oh, you listen here, you do-gooder!

746
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:25,420
Your Emil Strago
just killed my garage man

747
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:27,300
and physically assaulted my person.

748
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:29,707
He seems to think
that I have the painting.

749
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:30,820
What have you found?

750
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,180
Well, I will tell you that

751
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:34,460
there is more here than meets the eye.

752
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:36,660
No painting takes three months to clean,

753
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,180
so I believe that Bronwen

754
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:39,780
was working on the Goya

755
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:41,860
and discovered something underneath.

756
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:42,980
(SIRENS WAILING)

757
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:44,460
I should like to see
her studio immediately.

758
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:46,180
In the cars, quickly. Maurice, Oxford.

759
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:47,461
Yes, sir.

760
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:59,591
GARDENER: I've been helpin' out
Miss Fellworthy goin' on five years now.

761
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:02,184
Just keepin' the place tidy and whatnot.

762
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:06,146
You have been grossly overcompensated.

763
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,541
Her lover was no help.

764
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:09,620
Lover? Bronwen?

765
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:10,940
Yeah, a Duke.

766
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:13,268
No help whatsoever, randy bugger.

767
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:20,187
"Love... your... Bunny."

768
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,461
Love your Bunny?

769
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,780
(EXCLAIMS)

770
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:25,780
A child! She spawned a child!

771
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:28,100
The woman bred! What an odious thought.

772
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,301
Ugh.

773
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:31,300
- Mmm.
- Don't imbibe the crime scene.

774
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:33,780
I found her here,
sprawled over the table,

775
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,260
with an arrow out of her back.

776
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,700
Course you did, man,
because the assailant fired from here.

777
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:39,820
- No, from the window.
- With a spear gun.

778
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:41,980
- With a crossbow.
- He was left-handed.

779
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:44,023
- Jesus Christ.
- Ha!

780
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,540
- Is this how she was found?
- (GROANS)

781
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:48,340
- What are you doing?
- Oh, no. To the left a bit.

782
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:50,580
- Like this?
- Sorry, I meant to the right.

783
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:52,544
- Like this? Like this?
- (GROANS)

784
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,942
Are you quite finished buggering around?

785
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:56,945
- No.
- (MAURICE WHIMPERS)

786
